7:
It's for a "Selgir"? Defense Captain
who lives on
The-Island-at-the-End-of-the-Sea?
16:
Oh, glad we found you. Here's your
package!
18:
What happened to the guy who
usually runs this route? He on
vacation?
21:
We don't know, actually. We kinda
got this job out of the blue...
23:
You're not from around here, are
you?
I'm sorry.
31:
UGH! That reeks! The hell is IN that
box?
33:
Rotten fish. Someone wants me to
join 'em... In Davy Jones' locker.
39:
There. That's why you were given the
job.
40:
This float's completely isolated, cut
off from government protection.
Makes it easy pickings for pirates.
43: Captain! Enemy ship at two o'clock!
53:
We'll stick with you. Smarter than
running around like headless
chickens.
58:
Not bad. Guess you weren't dead
weight after all.
62:
You're Gaea's people, right? If you're
always under attack, why don't they
send more soldiers?
66:
Tending the wounded comes first. A
few sailors also fell overboard...
69:
Captain! We finished securing the
enemy ships and... You're gonna
want to see this for yourself.
74:
Lieutenant Bragé. I'm disappointed,
but not surprised.
79:
Wait, he's from Gaea too... Why's he
working with pirates?
81:
Guess you really wanted me out of
the way, Bragé.
84:
This always happens! Corrupt swine
have been trying to build a secret
sty here for years, since we're so far
out nobody cares.
86:
But the Captain won't have them or
their dirty money, so⁠—
90:
So they hire guns to kill him. Hmph. I
wouldn't call 'em swine. That's rude
to the pigs.
93:
Lies! Lies and libel, all of it! Where's
your proof?! Untie me now!
96:
You were found cowering amidst
corsairs. That is proof enough.
98:
SHUT YOUR FILTHY MOUTH! I am a
LIEUTENANT! I was born on the
mainland!
99:
You cannot TOUCH ME! You're no
more than filthy BILGE RATS,
spawned on these sickening waves!
112:
Selgir! Y-you wouldn't! There will be
consequences!
117:
It doesn't matter to me whether you
live or die. Either way, I have no
future here.
120:
You have one chance, Bragé. If you
wanna live, you better start talking.
127:
Seems I've sailed us straight into a
storm.
129:
No, Captain. You're what kept us on
the path of justice!
131:
You give me too much credit. Even
without me, you'll know your course.
137: Hey. Know where you're headed next?
140: I haven't given it much thought.
145:
Be a helluva lot more interesting
than driftin' alone on the waves.
147:
Doubt I need to ask, but everyone's
fine with Selgir joining, right?
152:
Of course. Selgir, you will be
welcome in Starview.
156: All right. I'll take you up on your offer.
159: Sailors, I swear I'll be back.
163: You better all be there for my return.
